 <br>
After many seasons of encouragement by the noble Hirtius Maximus, I find myself compelled to seek admission into the Random Acts of Kindness Guild.  I seek admission as the values and mission are completely in accord with those qualities which I find most desirable in playing EQ.  A nurse and teacher by RW trade, my characters embody those traits which I often find lacking in my daily life -- selflessness, eagerness to share new skills and experience, joy and enthusiasm, excitement over helping others succeed.  It has been my inclination from the very first to assist newcomers with orientation, knowledge, buffs, and small gifts (and, occassionally, an unexpected very large gift, simply for the wonder and thrill it produces).  While none of my characters have much to commend them from a financial or skill standpoint (16 Cleric, 12 Wizard, etc.) they are, as I recall, in realms seemingly quite lofty to the first-day player, and able to contribute quite a lot in terms of &quot;tips and tricks,&quot; survival skills, advice on how and where to practice and level, and so forth.  I would like to put these talents to work in the service of a guild which I know by reputation and experience to be above reproach -- Random Acts of Kindness.  Thank you for your consideration!<br>
 <br>
Ahaf<br>
