<br>
Hirtius Maximus (31 paladin) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/brandomacts.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aenorn>aenorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Volunteer<br><font color=blue>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#006400>(8/2/01 1:16:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Thank you for your application</span><hr size=1> Greetings Ahaf,<br>
<br>
Thank you for applying for membership of our guild and may I take this opportunity to wish you success in your application.  <br>
<br>
We have an application procedure that you will be required to complete in order to enter into full membership of the guild.  I have listed the steps below.<br>
<br>
1. Apply in this forum  ( check!)<br>
<br>
2. Read the Call and Charter.  <br>
The Call and Charter detail the principles that our guild are based upon and to proceed you should be in broad agreement with them.  You can find details of them at  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqrandomacts.com">www.eqrandomacts.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
3. Attend Random Acts Events<br>
There are three main reasons for this, it is fun, you get to meet lots of guild members and most importantly you will need to seek out a sponsor.<br>
Details of upcoming events can be found on this message board under ?Hunting And Gathering?<br>
<br>
4. Find a Sponsor<br>
A sponsor is a regular guild member that will mentor you through the fledgling quest and support you in your application.  It is also hoped that you will form a special relationship with your sponsor.  Your sponsor will also be responsible for you.  You can find who is on at any one time by typing the command &lt;/who all random&gt; <br>
(Note: Guild members can sponsor more than one fledgling.)<br>
<br>
5. Fledgling Quest<br>
Details of the quest can be found at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqrandomacts.com">www.eqrandomacts.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and don?t be afraid of asking your sponsor for assistance and advice.<br>
6. Guild Tagging <br>
Upon successful completion of your Quest, your sponsor must notify Meriel Silvertree or Gwion Llwellyn either by posting here on the board, or through a tell in game,  you will then receive your Random Acts Tag at the next scheduled First Aid Camp (FA).<br>
First Aid Camps are generally held every two weeks, the first one on a Saturday, and the next one on a Sunday.<br>
<br>
7. Probationary Membership<br>
Probationary Membership will last until you attend the *next* regularly scheduled FA and barring any difficulties you will be accepted into the guild as a full member.<br>
<br>
8. Alternate Characters<br>
You will be able to have one alternate character tagged every two weeks.<br>
<br>
<br>
The road is long Fledgling, but you will find assistance, advice and kindness upon the way.  <br>
<br>
If you have any difficulties you may contact me at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: AenornDraggonFach@surefellGlade.plus.com "> AenornDraggonFach@surefellGlade.plus.com </a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--> or the council at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: eqrandomacts@hotmail.com"> eqrandomacts@hotmail.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--><br>
<br>
My advice is to you is to be proactive and seek out guild members near you both in Norrath and here upon the boards.  <br>
<br>
For  our records it would be helpful if you could provide us with details of your name, class, race, level, playing times, and e-mail address if you have not yet done so.<br>
<br>
Kind regards<br>
<br>
Aenorn DraggonFach<br>
Ranger Of Surefell Glade<br>
